sleV2M4RouteInfoActivity.name: sleV2M4RouteInfoActivity
sleV2M4RouteInfoActivity.description: Enable/disable status of multicast routing on this router.

sleV2M4RouteInfoLimit.name: sleV2M4RouteInfoLimit
sleV2M4RouteInfoLimit.description: Limiting number of multicast routes that can be added to a multicast routing table.

sleV2M4RouteInfoThreshold.name: sleV2M4RouteInfoThreshold
sleV2M4RouteInfoThreshold.description: Threshold number at which to generate a warning message.

sleV2M4RouteInfoUnknownFlood.name: sleV2M4RouteInfoUnknownFlood
sleV2M4RouteInfoUnknownFlood.description: Flooding status of unknown multicast packets on this router.

sleV2M4RouteInfoEntryCount.name: sleV2M4RouteInfoEntryCount
sleV2M4RouteInfoEntryCount.description: The number of rows in the sleV2MRoute4Table. This can be used to monitor the multicast routing table size

sleV2M4RouteInfoNocacheRecvMsg.name: sleV2M4RouteInfoNocacheRecvMsg
sleV2M4RouteInfoNocacheRecvMsg.description: The number of all NOCACHE event messages which this MRIB has received from the Multicast Forwarder for all entries. The Multicast Forwarder generates the NOCACHE event when it receives a data packet destined to (S,G), and does not have an (S,G) MRT entry.

sleV2M4RouteInfoWholepktRecvMsg.name: sleV2M4RouteInfoWholepktRecvMsg
sleV2M4RouteInfoWholepktRecvMsg.description: The number of all WHOLEPKT event messages which this MRIB has received from the Multicast Forwarder for all entries. The Multicast Forwarder generates the WHOLEPKT event whenever the special REGISTER VIF appears in the out interface list of an (S,G) MRT in the multicast forwarder.

sleV2M4RouteInfoWrongvifRecvMsg.name: sleV2M4RouteInfoWrongvifRecvMsg
sleV2M4RouteInfoWrongvifRecvMsg.description: The number of all WRONGVIF event messages which this MRIB has received from the Multicast Forwarder for all entries. The Multicast Forwarder generates a WRONGVIF event when it receives a packet destined to (S,G) on an interface that does not match the IIF of the (S,G) MRT in the Multicast Forwarder.

sleV2M4RouteInfoNocacheSentMsg.name: sleV2M4RouteInfoNocacheSentMsg
sleV2M4RouteInfoNocacheSentMsg.description: The number of all NSM_MSG_IPV4_MRT_NOCACHE(NSM_MSG_IPV6_MRT_NOCACHE) messages which MRIB sent to multicast protocol for all entries. When the MRIB receives NOCACHE event message from Multicast Forwarder, it relays it to all multicast protocols, ensuring that the correct multicast protocol adds an (S,G) MRT to the MRIB.

sleV2M4RouteInfoWholepktSentMsg.name: sleV2M4RouteInfoWholepktSentMsg
sleV2M4RouteInfoWholepktSentMsg.description: The number of all NSM_MSG_IPV4_MRT_WHOLEPKT_REQUEST(NSM_MSG_IPV6_MRT_WHOLEPKT_REQUEST) messages which MRIB sent to multicast protocol for all entries. When the MRIB receives WHOLEPKT event message from Multicast Forwarder, it sends an message to the multicast protocol. It is inefficient and expensive to relay this whole message to the multicast protocol, because IP packet can be as large as 64 KB. To avoid sending the WHOLEPKT message to the multicast protocol, NSM_MSG_IPV4_MRT_WHOLEPKT_REQUEST message contains the (S,G) key, the REGISTER VIF index, and a unique identifier for the instance of the WHOLEPKT message from the Multicast Forwarder, whitout the all packet data.

sleV2M4RouteInfoWrongvifSentMsg.name: sleV2M4RouteInfoWrongvifSentMsg
sleV2M4RouteInfoWrongvifSentMsg.description: The number of all NSM_MSG_IPV4_MRT_WRONGVIF(NSM_MSG_IPV6_MRT_WRONGVIF) messages which MRIB sent to multicast protocol for all entries. When the MRIB receives WRONGVIF event message from Multicast Forwarder, it relays it to all multicast protocols that have requested PIM service.

sleV2M4RoutInfoIpMrouteJoinedCount.name: sleV2M4RoutInfoIpMrouteJoinedCount
sleV2M4RoutInfoIpMrouteJoinedCount.description: The count of Mroute Joined channel

sleV2M4RouteInfoControlRequest.name: sleV2M4RouteInfoControlRequest
sleV2M4RouteInfoControlRequest.description: The request of a user command

sleV2M4RouteInfoControlTimer.name: sleV2M4RouteInfoControlTimer
sleV2M4RouteInfoControlTimer.description: The maximum time for the manager for a long running user command

sleV2M4RouteInfoControlTimeStamp.name: sleV2M4RouteInfoControlTimeStamp
sleV2M4RouteInfoControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command(end of command)

sleV2M4RouteInfoControlReqResult.name: sleV2M4RouteInfoControlReqResult
sleV2M4RouteInfoControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command

sleV2M4RouteInfoControlLimit.name: sleV2M4RouteInfoControlLimit
sleV2M4RouteInfoControlLimit.description: CLI:(no) ip multicast route-limit LIMIT (THRESHOLD) value(-1) : (no)

sleV2M4RouteInfoControlThreshold.name: sleV2M4RouteInfoControlThreshold
sleV2M4RouteInfoControlThreshold.description: CLI:(no) ip multicast route-limit LIMIT (THRESHOLD) value(-1) : (no)

sleV2M4RouteTable.name: sleV2M4RouteTable
sleV2M4RouteTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing multicast routing information for IP datagrams sent by particular sources to the IP multicast groups known to this router.

sleV2M4RouteEntry.name: sleV2M4RouteEntry
sleV2M4RouteEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the multicast routing information for IP datagrams from a particular source and addressed to a particular IP multicast group address. Discontinuities in counters in this entry can be detected by observing the value of sleV2M4RouteUpTime. key: sleV2M4RouteGroup, sleV2M4RouteSource, sleV2M4RouteSrcMask

sleV2M4RouteGroup.name: sleV2M4RouteGroup
sleV2M4RouteGroup.description: The IP multicast group address for which this entry contains multicast routing information.

sleV2M4RouteSource.name: sleV2M4RouteSource
sleV2M4RouteSource.description: The network address which when combined with the corresponding value of ipMRouteSourceMask identifies the sources for which this entry contains multicast routing information. For (*,G) entry, value 0.0.0.0

sleV2M4RouteSrcMask.name: sleV2M4RouteSrcMask
sleV2M4RouteSrcMask.description: The network mask which when combined with the corresponding value of sleV2M4RouteSource identifies the sources for which this entry contains multicast routing information. For (*,G) entry, value 0.0.0.0

sleV2M4RouteInInterface.name: sleV2M4RouteInInterface
sleV2M4RouteInInterface.description: The value of ifIndex for the interface on which IP datagrams sent by these sources to this multicast address are received. A value of 0 indicates that datagrams are not subject to an incoming interface check, but may be accepted on multiple interfaces (e.g., in CBT).

sleV2M4RouteUpstreamNeighbor.name: sleV2M4RouteUpstreamNeighbor
sleV2M4RouteUpstreamNeighbor.description: The address of the upstream neighbor (e.g., RPF neighbor) from which IP datagrams from these sources to this multicast address are received, or 0.0.0.0 if the upstream neighbor is unknown (e.g., in CBT).

sleV2M4RouteUpTime.name: sleV2M4RouteUpTime
sleV2M4RouteUpTime.description: The time since the multicast routing information represented by this entry was learned by the router.

sleV2MRouteExpiryTime.name: sleV2MRouteExpiryTime
sleV2MRouteExpiryTime.description: The minimum amount of time remaining before this entry will be aged out. The value 0 indicates that the entry is not subject to aging.

sleV2M4RouteMcProtocol.name: sleV2M4RouteMcProtocol
sleV2M4RouteMcProtocol.description: The multicast routing protocol via which this multicast forwarding entry was learned.

sleV2M4RouteRtProtocol.name: sleV2M4RouteRtProtocol
sleV2M4RouteRtProtocol.description: The routing mechanism via which the route used to find the upstream or parent interface for this multicast forwarding entry was learned. Inclusion of values for routing protocols is not intended to imply that those protocols need be supported.

sleV2M4RouteRtAddress.name: sleV2M4RouteRtAddress
sleV2M4RouteRtAddress.description: The address portion of the route used to find the upstream or parent interface for this multicast forwarding entry.

sleV2M4RouteRtMask.name: sleV2M4RouteRtMask
sleV2M4RouteRtMask.description: The mask associated with the route used to find the upstream or parent interface for this multicast forwarding entry.

sleV2M4RouteRtType.name: sleV2M4RouteRtType
sleV2M4RouteRtType.description: The reason the given route was placed in the (logical) multicast Routing Information Base (RIB). A value of unicast means that the route would normally be placed only in the unicast RIB, but was placed in the multicast RIB (instead or in addition) due to local configuration, such as when running PIM over RIP. A value of multicast means that the route was explicitly added to the multicast RIB by the routing protocol, such as DVMRP or Multiprotocol BGP.

sleV2M4RouteOutIfCount.name: sleV2M4RouteOutIfCount
sleV2M4RouteOutIfCount.description: The number of entry's outgoing interfaces.

sleV2M4RouteOutInterface.name: sleV2M4RouteOutInterface
sleV2M4RouteOutInterface.description: The bitmap of entry's outgoing interfaces.

sleV2M4RouteStsFwdPkts.name: sleV2M4RouteStsFwdPkts
sleV2M4RouteStsFwdPkts.description: The number of packets which this router has received from these sources and addressed to this multicast group address, and which were forwarded by this router.

sleV2M4RouteStsFwdBytes.name: sleV2M4RouteStsFwdBytes
sleV2M4RouteStsFwdBytes.description: The number of octets contained in IP datagrams which were received from these sources and addressed to this multicast group address, and which were forwarded by this router.

sleV2M4RouteStsWrongIfPkts.name: sleV2M4RouteStsWrongIfPkts
sleV2M4RouteStsWrongIfPkts.description: The number of packets which this router has received from these sources and addressed to this multicast group address, which were dropped because they were not received on the interface indicated by sleV2M4RouteInInterface. Packets which are not subject to an incoming interface check (e.g., using CBT) are not counted.

sleV2M4RouteStsWholepktRecvMsg.name: sleV2M4RouteStsWholepktRecvMsg
sleV2M4RouteStsWholepktRecvMsg.description: The number of WHOLEPKT event messages which this MRIB has received from the Multicast Forwarder for this entry. The Multicast Forwarder generates the WHOLEPKT event whenever the special REGISTER VIF appears in the out interface list of an (S,G) MRT in the multicast forwarder.

sleV2M4RouteStsWrongvifRecvMsg.name: sleV2M4RouteStsWrongvifRecvMsg
sleV2M4RouteStsWrongvifRecvMsg.description: The number of WRONGVIF event messages which this MRIB has received from the Multicast Forwarder for this entry. The Multicast Forwarder generates a WRONGVIF event when it receives a packet destined to (S,G) on an interface that does not match the IIF of the (S,G) MRT in the Multicast Forwarder.

sleV2M4RouteStsWholepktSentMsg.name: sleV2M4RouteStsWholepktSentMsg
sleV2M4RouteStsWholepktSentMsg.description: The number of NSM_MSG_IPV4_MRT_WHOLEPKT_REQUEST(NSM_MSG_IPV6_MRT_WHOLEPKT_REQUEST) messages which MRIB sent to multicast protocol for this entry. When the MRIB receives WHOLEPKT event message from Multicast Forwarder, it sends an message to the multicast protocol. It is inefficient and expensive to relay this whole message to the multicast protocol, because IP packet can be as large as 64 KB. To avoid sending the WHOLEPKT message to the multicast protocol, NSM_MSG_IPV4_MRT_WHOLEPKT_REQUEST message contains the (S,G) key, the REGISTER VIF index, and a unique identifier for the instance of the WHOLEPKT message from the Multicast Forwarder, whitout the all packet data.

sleV2M4RouteStsWrongvifSentMsg.name: sleV2M4RouteStsWrongvifSentMsg
sleV2M4RouteStsWrongvifSentMsg.description: The number of NSM_MSG_IPV4_MRT_WRONGVIF(NSM_MSG_IPV6_MRT_WRONGVIF) messages which MRIB sent to multicast protocol for this entry. When the MRIB receives WRONGVIF event message from Multicast Forwarder, it relays it to all multicast protocols that have requested PIM service.

sleV2M4RouteStsTimedSentMsg.name: sleV2M4RouteStsTimedSentMsg
sleV2M4RouteStsTimedSentMsg.description: The number of notification messages occured by timed event of MRIB by which multicast protocols update own statistics information.

sleV2M4RouteStsImmediateSentMsg.name: sleV2M4RouteStsImmediateSentMsg
sleV2M4RouteStsImmediateSentMsg.description: The number of notification messages occured by immediate event of MRIB by which multicast protocols update own statistics information.

sleV2M4RouteStsRegAckRecvMsg.name: sleV2M4RouteStsRegAckRecvMsg
sleV2M4RouteStsRegAckRecvMsg.description: The number of ACK messages which the MRIB has received from multicast protocol for this MRIB entry, and by which MRIB originates a Register packet to the destination RP provided in this ACK reply.

sleV2M4RouteStsRegNackRecvMsg.name: sleV2M4RouteStsRegNackRecvMsg
sleV2M4RouteStsRegNackRecvMsg.description: The number of NACK messages which the MRIB has received from multicast protocol for this MRIB entry, and by which MRIB don't originates a Register packet to the destination RP provided in this ACK reply.

sleV2M4RouteStsRegSentPkts.name: sleV2M4RouteStsRegSentPkts
sleV2M4RouteStsRegSentPkts.description: The number of Register packets which the MRIB sent to the destination RP for this entry.

sleV2M4RouteControlRequest.name: sleV2M4RouteControlRequest
sleV2M4RouteControlRequest.description: The request of a user command

sleV2M4RouteControlTimer.name: sleV2M4RouteControlTimer
sleV2M4RouteControlTimer.description: The maximum time for the manager for a long running user command

sleV2M4RouteControlTimeStamp.name: sleV2M4RouteControlTimeStamp
sleV2M4RouteControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command(end of command)

sleV2M4RouteControlReqResult.name: sleV2M4RouteControlReqResult
sleV2M4RouteControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command

sleV2M4RouteControlGroup.name: sleV2M4RouteControlGroup
sleV2M4RouteControlGroup.description: The IP multicast group address for which this entry contains multicast routing information.

sleV2M4RouteControlSource.name: sleV2M4RouteControlSource
sleV2M4RouteControlSource.description: The network address which when combined with the corresponding value of ipMRouteSourceMask identifies the sources for which this entry contains multicast routing information. For (*,G) entry, value 0.0.0.0

sleV2M4RouteControlSrcMask.name: sleV2M4RouteControlSrcMask
sleV2M4RouteControlSrcMask.description: The network mask which when combined with the corresponding value of sleV2M4RouteSource identifies the sources for which this entry contains multicast routing information. For (*,G) entry, value 0.0.0.0

sleV2M4RouteControlMcastProtocol.name: sleV2M4RouteControlMcastProtocol
sleV2M4RouteControlMcastProtocol.description: The multicast routing protocol via which this multicast forwarding entry was learned.

sleV2M4RouteNextHopTable.name: sleV2M4RouteNextHopTable
sleV2M4RouteNextHopTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing information on the next-hops on outgoing interfaces for routing IP multicast datagrams. Each entry is one of a list of next-hops on outgoing interfaces for particular sources sending to a particular multicast group address.

sleV2M4RouteNextHopEntry.name: sleV2M4RouteNextHopEntry
sleV2M4RouteNextHopEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the list of next-hops on outgoing interfaces to which IP multicast datagrams from particular sources to a IP multicast group address are routed. Discontinuities in counters in this entry can be detected by observing the value of sleV2M4RouteUpTime. key: sleV2M4RouteGroup, sleV2M4RouteSource, sleV2M4RouteSrcMask, sleV2M4RouteNextHopIfIndex, sleV2M4RouteNextHopAddress

sleV2M4RouteNextHopIfIndex.name: sleV2M4RouteNextHopIfIndex
sleV2M4RouteNextHopIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the interface for the outgoing interface for this next-hop.

sleV2M4RouteNextHopAddress.name: sleV2M4RouteNextHopAddress
sleV2M4RouteNextHopAddress.description: The address of the next-hop specific to this entry. For most interfaces, this is identical to sleV2M4RouteGroup. NBMA interfaces, however, may have multiple next-hop addresses out a single outgoing interface.

sleV2M4RouteNextHopState.name: sleV2M4RouteNextHopState
sleV2M4RouteNextHopState.description: An indication of whether the outgoing interface and next- hop represented by this entry is currently being used to forward IP datagrams. The value 'forwarding' indicates it is currently being used; the value 'pruned' indicates it is not.

sleV2M4RouteNextHopUpTime.name: sleV2M4RouteNextHopUpTime
sleV2M4RouteNextHopUpTime.description: The time since the multicast routing information represented by this entry was learned by the router.

sleV2M4RouteNextHopExpiryTime.name: sleV2M4RouteNextHopExpiryTime
sleV2M4RouteNextHopExpiryTime.description: The minimum amount of time remaining before this entry will be aged out. If ipMRouteNextHopState is pruned(1), the remaining time until the prune expires and the state reverts to forwarding(2). Otherwise, the remaining time until this entry is removed from the table. The time remaining may be copied from sleV2MRouteExpiryTime if the protocol in use for this entry does not specify next-hop timers. The value 0 indicates that the entry is not subject to aging.

sleV2M4RouteNextHopProtocol.name: sleV2M4RouteNextHopProtocol
sleV2M4RouteNextHopProtocol.description: The routing mechanism via which this next-hop was learned.

sleV2M4RouteNextHopClosestMemberHops.name: sleV2M4RouteNextHopClosestMemberHops
sleV2M4RouteNextHopClosestMemberHops.description: The minimum number of hops between this router and any member of this IP multicast group reached via this next-hop on this outgoing interface. Any IP multicast datagrams for the group which have a TTL less than this number of hops will not be forwarded to this next-hop.

sleV2M4RouteNextHopPkts.name: sleV2M4RouteNextHopPkts
sleV2M4RouteNextHopPkts.description: The number of packets which have been forwarded using this route.

sleV2M4RouteIfTable.name: sleV2M4RouteIfTable
sleV2M4RouteIfTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing multicast routing information specific to interfaces.

sleV2M4RouteIfEntry.name: sleV2M4RouteIfEntry
sleV2M4RouteIfEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the multicast routing information for a particular interface. key: sleV2M4RouteIfIndex

sleV2M4RouteIfIndex.name: sleV2M4RouteIfIndex
sleV2M4RouteIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the interface for which this entry contains information.

sleV2M4RouteIfName.name: sleV2M4RouteIfName
sleV2M4RouteIfName.description: The ifName of the interface for which this entry contains information.

sleV2M4RouteIfTtl.name: sleV2M4RouteIfTtl
sleV2M4RouteIfTtl.description: The datagram TTL threshold for the interface. Any IP multicast datagrams with a TTL less than this threshold will not be forwarded out the interface. The default value of 0 means all multicast packets are forwarded out the interface.

sleV2M4RouteIfRateLimit.name: sleV2M4RouteIfRateLimit
sleV2M4RouteIfRateLimit.description: The rate-limit, in kilobits per second, of forwarded multicast traffic on the interface. A rate-limit of 0 indicates that no rate limiting is done.

sleV2M4RouteIfProtocol.name: sleV2M4RouteIfProtocol
sleV2M4RouteIfProtocol.description: The routing protocol running on this interface.

sleV2M4RouteIfInMcastOctets.name: sleV2M4RouteIfInMcastOctets
sleV2M4RouteIfInMcastOctets.description: The number of octets of multicast packets that have arrived on the interface, including framing characters. This object is similar to ifInOctets in the Interfaces MIB, except that only multicast packets are counted.

sleV2M4RouteIfOutMcastOctets.name: sleV2M4RouteIfOutMcastOctets
sleV2M4RouteIfOutMcastOctets.description: The number of octets of multicast packets that have been sent on the interface.

sleV2M4RouteIfControlRequest.name: sleV2M4RouteIfControlRequest
sleV2M4RouteIfControlRequest.description: The request of a user command

sleV2M4RouteIfControlTimer.name: sleV2M4RouteIfControlTimer
sleV2M4RouteIfControlTimer.description: The maximum time for the manager for a long running user command

sleV2M4RouteIfControlTimeStamp.name: sleV2M4RouteIfControlTimeStamp
sleV2M4RouteIfControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command(end of command)

sleV2M4RouteIfControlReqResult.name: sleV2M4RouteIfControlReqResult
sleV2M4RouteIfControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command

sleV2M4RouteIfControlIndex.name: sleV2M4RouteIfControlIndex
sleV2M4RouteIfControlIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the interface for which this control changes multicast configuration.

sleV2M4RouteIfControlTtl.name: sleV2M4RouteIfControlTtl
sleV2M4RouteIfControlTtl.description: The datagram TTL threshold for the interface. Any IP multicast datagrams with a TTL less than this threshold will not be forwarded out the interface. The default value of 0 means all multicast packets are forwarded out the interface.

sleV2M4RouteIfControlRateLimit.name: sleV2M4RouteIfControlRateLimit
sleV2M4RouteIfControlRateLimit.description: The rate-limit, in kilobits per second, of forwarded multicast traffic on the interface. A rate-limit of 0 indicates that no rate limiting is done.

sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopActivity.name: sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopActivity
sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopActivity.description: This object indicates whether IGMP Snooping has been enabled for the system.

sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopVersion.name: sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopVersion
sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopVersion.description: The maximum version of IGMP supported.

sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopFastLeave.name: sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopFastLeave
sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopFastLeave.description: This object indicates whether Fast-Leave mechanism has been configured to be enabled in the system. If Fast-Leave is enabled in the switch, IGMP Snooping will prune the port on which an IGMP leave message has been received without waiting for the Group Specific Query to timeout to determine whether there are any more hosts on that port for that group. If the value of sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopVersion is not 3, this object will not have any effect.

sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopFastBlock.name: sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopFastBlock
sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopFastBlock.description: The object indicates whether Fast-Block mechanism has been enabled for the system. This object only has effect if the value of sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopVersion is 3.

sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopReportSuppression.name: sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopReportSuppression
sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopReportSuppression.description: When this object is set to 'true', IGMP Snooping will suppress duplicate IGMP Reports. When this object is set to 'false', all IGMP Reports are forwarded to all multicast routers. Alias is IGMP Snooping Proxy.

sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopQuerierActivity.name: sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopQuerierActivity
sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopQuerierActivity.description: The object indicates whether the device will participate in the IGMP Querier election. If the object is set to 'true', the device will participate to an election process to be a Querier.

sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopQueryInterval.name: sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopQueryInterval
sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopQueryInterval.description: The frequency at which IGMP packets are transmitted on this interface.

sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopMaxResponseTime.name: sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopMaxResponseTime
sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopMaxResponseTime.description: The maximum query response time advertised in queries on this interface.

sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopLastMembQueryIntvl.name: sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopLastMembQueryIntvl
sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopLastMembQueryIntvl.description: The Last Member Qury Interval is the Max Response Time inserted into Group-Specific Queries sent in response to Leave Group messages, and is also the amount of time Between Group-Specific Query messages. This value may be tuned to modify the leave latency of the network. A reduced value results in reduced time to detect the loss of the last member of a group. The value of this object is irrelevant if mgmdRouterInterfaceVersion is 1

sleV2IgmpInfoTcnFloodActivity.name: sleV2IgmpInfoTcnFloodActivity
sleV2IgmpInfoTcnFloodActivity.description: TRUE is multicast traffic will be flooded on all ports of the VLAN for TcnFloodQueryCount of IGMP General Queries upon receiving a Topology Change Notification (TCN) for the VLAN. FALSE is not flooding.

sleV2IgmpInfoTcnQuerySolicitActivity.name: sleV2IgmpInfoTcnQuerySolicitActivity
sleV2IgmpInfoTcnQuerySolicitActivity.description: This object specifies whether the device running IGMP Snooping will solicit IGMP General Queries from the Querier upon receiving a Topology Change Notification (TCN). The root device will always solicit IGMP General Queries on TCN irrespective of the value of this.

sleV2IgmpInfoTcnFloodQueryCount.name: sleV2IgmpInfoTcnFloodQueryCount
sleV2IgmpInfoTcnFloodQueryCount.description: This object specifies the flooding period for multicast traffic upon receiving Topology Change Notifications (TCN). IGMP Snooping will flood multicast traffic until this count number of IGMP General Queries are received by IGMP Snooping.

sleV2IgmpInfoExplicitTracking.name: sleV2IgmpInfoExplicitTracking
sleV2IgmpInfoExplicitTracking.description: In IGMPv3, it decide the device tracks reporters or not.

sleV2IgmpInfoTcnQuerySolicitAddress.name: sleV2IgmpInfoTcnQuerySolicitAddress
sleV2IgmpInfoTcnQuerySolicitAddress.description: The source adddress of TCN solicit

sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopExplicitTrackingMacBas.name: sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopExplicitTrackingMacBased
sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopExplicitTrackingMacBas.description: In IGMPv3, it decide the mac-based device tracks reporters or not.

sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopTcnQueryGeneralStatus.name: sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopTcnQueryGeneralStatus
sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopTcnQueryGeneralStatus.description: The status is indicated Generating an IGMPv2 gereral query.

sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopTcnQueryGeneralMaxResp.name: sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopTcnQueryGeneralMaxResponseTime
sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopTcnQueryGeneralMaxResp.description: IGMP Snooping general query maximum response time (1-25sec, Default:1sec). when the TCN query general status is disable, max reponse time is 0.

sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopMRtLearningMode.name: sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopMRtLearningMode
sleV2IgmpInfoSnoopMRtLearningMode.description: This object specifies the multicast router port learning method for IGMP Snooping none(0): don't learning, Only use static router ports. pim(1) : Protocol Independent Multicast.

sleV2IgmpInfoSsmMapActive.name: sleV2IgmpInfoSsmMapActive
sleV2IgmpInfoSsmMapActive.description: Use this command to enable SSM mapping on the router.

sleV2IgmpInfoLimit.name: sleV2IgmpInfoLimit
sleV2IgmpInfoLimit.description: Use this command to set the maximum number of group membership states, at either the router level or at the interface level. range : 1 ~ 2097152 0 : disable

sleV2IgmpInfoLimitExcept.name: sleV2IgmpInfoLimitExcept
